						<div class="postbody">The absolute easiest thing would be short example code.  It really wouldn't have to be that long.  There's a link to some of tokumaru's code but we don't get to see what's in each variable.
<br />
<br />An example like, here is a game with a status bar at the top, the player has just started playing and has triggered the first pixel of horizontal movement.  Timed code has gotten us to this point, here are several variables and exactly what they contain, and here is a routine showing how to scroll 1 pixel over.
<br />
<br />I realize it's important to understand the underpinnings, but some people learn better this way.
<br />
<br />EDIT: On further review, tokumaru's code and the rest of the links (Shiru's vertical scroll question) are already very educational, but again, literally showing values being written and when to write them can also be informative.</div>

